#: ay_bigfile.xml:408
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a Control File"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:412
#, no-c-format
msgid "Collecting Information"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:414
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create the control file, you need to collect information about the "
"systems you are going to install. This includes hardware data and network "
"information among other things. Make sure you have the following information "
"about the machines you want to install:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:423
#, no-c-format
msgid "Hard disk types and sizes"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:428
#, no-c-format
msgid "Graphical interface and attached monitor, if any"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:433
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Network interface and MAC address if known (for example, when using DHCP)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:441
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using the Configuration Management System (CMS)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:443
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create the control file for one or more computers, a configuration "
"interface based on &yast; is provided. This system depends on existing "
"modules which are usually used to configure a computer in regular operation "
"mode, for example, after &productname; is installed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:451
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The configuration management system lets you easily create control files and "
"manage a repository of configurations for the use in a networked environment "
"with multiple clients."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:470
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuration System"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:482
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a New Control File"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:483
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With some exceptions, almost all resources of the control file can be "
"configured using the configuration management system. The system offers "
"flexibility and the configuration of some resources is identical to the one "
"available in the &yast; control center. In addition to the existing and "
"familiar modules new interfaces were created for special and complex "
"configurations, for example for partitioning, general options and software."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:492
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Furthermore, using a CMS guarantees the validity of the resulting control "
"file and its direct use for starting automated installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:496
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure the configuration system is installed (package <systemitem class="
"\"resource\">autoyast2</systemitem> ) and call it using the &yast; control "
"center or as root with the following command (make sure the <envar>DISPLAY</"
"envar> variable is set correctly to start the graphical user interface "
"instead of the text-based one):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:503
#, no-c-format
msgid "/sbin/yast2 autoyast"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:507
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating/Editing a Control File Manually"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:509
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If editing the control file manually, make sure it has a valid syntax. To "
"check the syntax, use the tools already available on the distribution. For "
"example, to verify that the file is well-formed (has a valid XML structure), "
"use the utility <command>xmllint</command> available with the "
"<systemitem>libxml2</systemitem> package:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:517
#, no-c-format
msgid "xmllint &lt;control file&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:519
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the control file is not well formed, for example, if a tag is not closed, "
"<command>xmllint</command> will report the errors."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:525
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To validate the control file, use the tool <command>jing</command> from the "
"package with the same name. During validation misplaced or missing tags and "
"attributes and wrong attribute values are detected. <phrase os=\"sles\">the "
"package <package>jing</package> is provided with the &sdk;.</phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:533
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"jing /usr/share/YaST2/schema/autoyast/rng/profile.rng &lt;control file&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:535
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>/usr/share/YaST2/schema/autoyast/rng/profile.rng</literal> is "
"provided by the package <literal>yast2-schema</literal> . This file "
"describes the syntax and classes of an &ay; profile."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:542
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before going on with the autoinstallation, fix any errors resulting from "
"such checks. The autoinstallation process cannot be started with an invalid "
"and not well-formed control file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:548
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use any XML editor available on your system or any text editor with "
"XML support (for example, Emacs, Vim). However, it is not optimal to create "
"the control file manually for many machines and it should only be seen as an "
"interface between the autoinstallation engine and the Configuration "
"Management System (CMS)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:557
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using Emacs as an XML Editor"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:558
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The built-in nxml-mode turns Emacs into a fully-fledged XML editor with "
"automatic tag completion and validation. Refer to the Emacs help for "
"instructions on how to set up nxml-mode."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:566
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a Control File via Script with XSLT"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:568
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have a template and want to change a few things via script or command "
"line, use an XSLT processor like <literal>xsltproc</literal> . For example, "
"if you have an &ay; control file and want to fill out the host name via "
"script for any reason (if doing this so often, you want to script it)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:576
#, no-c-format
msgid "First, create an XSL file"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:581
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example File for Replacing the Host Name/Domain by Script"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:582
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?&gt;\n"
"&lt;xsl:stylesheet xmlns:xsl=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform\"\n"
"  xmlns:y2=\"http://www.suse.com/1.0/yast2ns\"\n"
"  xmlns:config=\"http://www.suse.com/1.0/configns\"\n"
"  xmlns=\"http://www.suse.com/1.0/yast2ns\"\n"
"  version=\"1.0\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;xsl:output method=\"xml\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" indent=\"yes\" omit-xml-"
"declaration=\"no\" cdata-section-elements=\"source\"/&gt;\n"
"\n"
"  &lt;!-- the parameter names --&gt;\n"
"  &lt;xsl:param name=\"hostname\"/&gt;\n"
"  &lt;xsl:param name=\"domain\"/&gt;\n"
"\n"
"  &lt;xsl:template match=\"/\"&gt;\n"
"    &lt;xsl:apply-templates select=\"@*|node()\"/&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/xsl:template&gt;\n"
"\n"
"  &lt;xsl:template match=\"y2:dns\"&gt;\n"
"    &lt;xsl:copy&gt;\n"
"      &lt;!-- where to copy the parameters --&gt;\n"
"      &lt;domain&gt;&lt;xsl:value-of select=\"string($domain)\"/&gt;&lt;/"
"domain&gt;\n"
"      &lt;hostname&gt;&lt;xsl:value-of select=\"string($hostname)\"/&gt;&lt;/"
"hostname&gt;\n"
"      &lt;xsl:apply-templates select=\"@*|node()\"/&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/xsl:copy&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/xsl:template&gt;\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"  &lt;xsl:template match=\"@*|node()\" &gt;\n"
"    &lt;xsl:copy&gt;\n"
"      &lt;xsl:apply-templates select=\"@*|node()\"/&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/xsl:copy&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/xsl:template&gt;\n"
"\n"
"&lt;/xsl:stylesheet&gt;\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:618
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This file expects the host name and the domain name as parameters from the "
"user."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:623
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;xsl:param name=\"hostname\"/&gt;\n"
"&lt;xsl:param name=\"domain\"/&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:626
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There will be a copy of those parameters in the dns section of the control "
"file. That means, if there already is a domain element in the dns section, "
"you will get a second one which is not good."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:661
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For more information about XSLT, go to the official Web page <link xlink:"
"href=\"http://www.w3.org/TR/xslt\">www.w3.org/TR/xslt</link>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:683
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuration and Installation Options"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:685
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter introduces important parts of a control file for standard "
"purposes. To learn about other available options, use the configuration "
"management system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:690
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that for some configuration options to work, additional packages need "
"to be installed, depending on the software selection you have configured. If "
"you choose to install a minimal system then some packages might be missing "
"and need to be added to the individual package selection."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:697
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&yast; will install packages required in the second phase of the "
"installation and before the post-installation phase of &ay; has started. "
"However, if necessary &yast; modules are not available in the system, "
"important configuration steps will be skipped. For example, no security "
"settings will be configured if <systemitem class=\"resource\">yast2-"
"security</systemitem> is not installed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:709
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"General options include all the settings related to the installation process "
"and the environment of the installed system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:714
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The mode section configures the behavior of &ay; with regard to confirmation "
"and rebooting. The following needs to be in the &lt;general&gt;&lt;mode&gt; "
"section."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:720
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default, the user must confirm the auto-installation process. This option "
"allows the user to view and change the settings for a target system before "
"they are committed and can be used for debugging. <literal>confirm</literal> "
"is set to <literal>true</literal> by default to avoid recursive installs "
"when the system schedules a reboot after initial system setup. Only disable "
"confirmation if you want to carry out a fully unattended installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:730
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With <literal>halt</literal> you cause &ay; to shut down the machine after "
"all packages have been installed. Instead of a reboot into stage two, the "
"machine is turned off. The boot loader is already installed and all your "
"chroot scripts have run."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:737
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>final_halt</literal> and <literal>final_reboot</literal> halts or "
"reboots the machine after the installation and the configuration are "
"finished at the end of stage 2."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:743
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>final_restart_services</literal> : After installation and "
"configuration are finished at the end of stage 2 all services will be "
"restarted by default. With this flag set to <literal>false</literal> no "
"restart will be done."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:750
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>activate_systemd_default_target</literal> : After installation and "
"configuration are finished at the end of stage 2 the default target system "
"will be activated."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:756
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>ntp_sync_time_before_installation</literal> specifies the NTP "
"server with which the system time needs to be synchronized before starting "
"the installation on the target system. It will not be synchronized if this "
"flag has not been used. Keep in mind that you need a reachable NTP server "
"and network connections while running the installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:764
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>max_systemd_wait</literal> specifies how long &ay; waits at most "
"for systemd to set up the default target. Normally you do not need to bother "
"with this entry. If it is not preset, a reasonable default (30 seconds) is "
"used."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:771
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some &opensuse; versions use the kexec feature and do not reboot anymore "
"between stage 1 and stage 2. With the <literal>forceboot</literal> option "
"you can force the reboot in case you need it for some reason. The value "
"<literal>true</literal> will reboot, <literal>false</literal> will not "
"reboot and a missing <literal>forceboot</literal> option uses the product's "
"default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:781
#, no-c-format
msgid "Drivers May Need a Reboot"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:782
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<remark>2013-03-18 - fs: bnc #802387</remark> Some drivers, for example the "
"proprietary drivers for Nvidia and ATI graphics cards, need a reboot and "
"will not work properly when using kexec. Therefore the default on "
"&productname; products is to always do a proper reboot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:815
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>confirm</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:820
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this boolean is set to <literal>true</literal> , the installation stops "
"at the confirmation screen (also called proposal screen) and needs to be "
"confirmed with the <guimenu>Install</guimenu> button."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:825
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;confirm config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;\n"
"  true\n"
"&lt;/confirm&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:837
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>halt</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:842
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Shuts down the machine after the first stage. So if you turn it on again, "
"the machine boots and the second stage of the autoinstallation starts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:847
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;halt config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;\n"
"  true\n"
"&lt;/halt&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:859
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>second_stage</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:864
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This boolean determines if &ay; will run in the second stage too (after the "
"partitioning, software and boot loader installation of the first stage). If "
"you set this to <literal>false</literal> , a normal manual installation "
"happens in the second stage."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:870
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;second_stage config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;\n"
"  true\n"
"&lt;/second_stage&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:882
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>final_reboot</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:887
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you set this to <literal>true</literal> , the machine will reboot at the "
"very end of the installation (when everything is installed and configured at "
"the end of the second stage)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:892
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;final_reboot config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;\n"
"  true\n"
"&lt;/final_reboot&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:897
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optional. The default is <literal>false</literal> . It makes no sense to set "
"this and <literal>final_halt</literal> to <literal>true</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:906
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>final_halt</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:911
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you set this to <literal>true</literal> , the machine will shut down at "
"the very end of the installation (when everything is installed and "
"configured at the end of the second stage)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:916
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;final_halt config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;\n"
"  true\n"
"&lt;/final_halt&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:921
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optional. The default is <literal>false</literal> . It makes no sense to set "
"this and <literal>final_reboot</literal> to <literal>true</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:930
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>confirm_base_product_license</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:935
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you set this to <literal>true</literal> , the EULA of the base product "
"will be shown. The user needs to accept this license. Otherwise the "
"installation will be canceled."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:940
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;confirm_base_product_license config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;\n"
"  true\n"
"&lt;/confirm_base_product_license&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:945
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optional. The default is <literal>false</literal> . This applies to the base "
"product license only. Use the flag <literal>confirm_license</literal> in the "
"<literal>add-on</literal> section to show additional licenses."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:955
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>final_restart_services</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:960
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you set this entry to <literal>false</literal> , all services will "
"<emphasis>not</emphasis> be restarted at the very end of the installation "
"(when everything is installed and configured at the end of the second stage)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:966
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;final_restart_services config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;\n"
"  false\n"
"&lt;/final_restart_services&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:978
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>activate_systemd_default_target</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:983
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you set this entry to <literal>false</literal> , the default target will "
"not be activated via the call <command>systemctl isolate</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:988
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;activate_systemd_default_target config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;\n"
"  false\n"
"&lt;/activate_systemd_default_target&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1000
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>forceboot</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1005
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some &opensuse; releases use kexec to avoid the reboot after the first "
"stage. They immediately boot into the installed system. You can force a "
"reboot with this:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1010
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;forceboot config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;\n"
"  true\n"
"&lt;/forceboot&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1022
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>self_update</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1027
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option allows to enable (set to <literal>true</literal> ) or disable "
"(set to <literal>false</literal> ) the self-update. Check out <xref linkend="
"\"sec.yast_install.self_update\"/> to find further information about this "
"feature."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1033
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;self_update config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;\n"
"  false\n"
"&lt;self_update/&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1047
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>self_update_url</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1052
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Location of the update repository to use during &yast; self-update. Check "
"out the &deploy; to find further information about this feature."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1057
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installer Self-Update Repository Only"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1058
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <option>self_update_url</option> parameter expects only the installer "
"self-update repository URL. Do not supply any other repository URL&mdash;for "
"example the URL of the software update repository."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1065
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;self_update_url&gt;\n"
"  http://example.com/updates/$arch\n"
"&lt;/self_update_url&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1068
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can specify the boot parameter <literal>self_update</"
"literal> on the kernel command line."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1072
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The URL can contain a variable <envar>$arch</envar> that will be replaced by "
"the system's architecture, such as <literal>x86_64</literal> , "
"<literal>s390x</literal> , etc."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1077
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the boot parameter <literal>self_update=1</literal> to enable the &yast; "
"self-update."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1087
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&ay; allows you to configure the proposal screen with the &lt;proposals "
"config:type=\"list\"&gt; option in the control file. All proposals that are "
"listed in that section are shown in the proposal screen if you set the "
"<literal>confirm</literal> option to <literal>true</literal> . Proposals are "
"also used during the regular installation and can be found in the file "
"<filename>control.xml</filename> in the root directory of the installation "
"media."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1099
#, no-c-format
msgid "General Options"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1100
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;general&gt;\n"
"  &lt;signature-handling&gt;\n"
"    &lt;accept_unsigned_file config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/"
"accept_unsigned_file&gt;\n"
"    &lt;accept_file_without_checksum config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/"
"accept_file_without_checksum&gt;\n"
"    &lt;accept_verification_failed config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/"
"accept_verification_failed&gt;\n"
"    &lt;accept_unknown_gpg_key config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/"
"accept_unknown_gpg_key&gt;\n"
"    &lt;import_gpg_key config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/"
"import_gpg_key&gt;\n"
"    &lt;accept_non_trusted_gpg_key config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/"
"accept_non_trusted_gpg_key&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/signature-handling&gt;\n"
"    &lt;cio_ignore config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;false&lt;/cio_ignore&gt;       "
"&lt;! -- &zseries; only --&gt;\n"
"  &lt;mode&gt;\n"
"    &lt;halt config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;false&lt;/halt&gt;\n"
"    &lt;forceboot config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;false&lt;/forceboot&gt;\n"
"    &lt;final_reboot config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;false&lt;/final_reboot&gt;\n"
"    &lt;final_halt config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;false&lt;/final_halt&gt;\n"
"    &lt;confirm_base_product_license config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;false&lt;/"
"confirm_base_product_license&gt;\n"
"    &lt;confirm config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/confirm&gt;\n"
"    &lt;second_stage config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/second_stage&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/mode&gt;\n"
"  &lt;self_update_url&gt;http://example.com/updates/$arch&lt;self_update_url/"
"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;proposals config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"    &lt;proposal&gt;partitions_proposal&lt;/proposal&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/proposals&gt;\n"
"  &lt;wait&gt;\n"
"    &lt;pre-modules config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"      &lt;module&gt;\n"
"        &lt;name&gt;networking&lt;/name&gt;\n"
"        &lt;sleep&gt;\n"
"          &lt;time config:type=\"integer\"&gt;10&lt;/time&gt;\n"
"          &lt;feedback config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/feedback&gt;\n"
"        &lt;/sleep&gt;\n"
"        &lt;script&gt;\n"
"          &lt;source&gt;sleep 5&lt;/source&gt;\n"
"          &lt;debug config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;false&lt;/debug&gt;\n"
"        &lt;/script&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/module&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/pre-modules&gt;\n"
"    &lt;post-modules config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"      &lt;module&gt;\n"
"        &lt;name&gt;networking&lt;/name&gt;\n"
"        &lt;sleep&gt;\n"
"          &lt;time config:type=\"integer\"&gt;3&lt;/time&gt;\n"
"          &lt;feedback config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/feedback&gt;\n"
"        &lt;/sleep&gt;\n"
"        &lt;script&gt;\n"
"          &lt;source&gt;sleep 7&lt;/source&gt;\n"
"          &lt;debug config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;false&lt;/debug&gt;\n"
"        &lt;/script&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/module&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/post-modules&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/wait&gt;\n"
"&lt;/general&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1154
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can let &ay; <command>sleep</command> before and after each module run "
"during the second stage. You can run scripts and/or pass a value (in "
"seconds) for &ay; to sleep. In the example above &ay; will sleep for 15 "
"seconds (10+5) before the network configuration starts and 10 seconds (3+7) "
"after the network configuration is done. The scripts in the example do not "
"really make a lot of sense because you could pass that value as <quote>time</"
"quote> value too. They are only used to show how scripts in the wait section "
"work now."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1165
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To blacklist devices, use the flag <literal>cio_ignore</literal> . This "
"option is available on &zseries; <emphasis>only</emphasis> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1171
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enabling Multipath for the Installation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1172
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When installing on a network storage that is accessed via multiple paths, "
"you need to enable multipath for the installation with the "
"<literal>start_multipath</literal> parameter. This parameter must be placed "
"within the following XML structure:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1178
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;general&gt;\n"
"  &lt;storage&gt;\n"
"    &lt;start_multipath config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/"
"start_multipath&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/storage&gt;\n"
"&lt;/general&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1183
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can pass the following parameter to linuxrc: "
"<literal>LIBSTORAGE_MULTIPATH_AUTOSTART=ON</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1190
#, no-c-format
msgid "Handling Installer Self-Update Signatures"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1191
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Installer updates are delivered using a dedicated repository, so the same "
"security checks that are applied to other repositories and packages are "
"performed on these updates."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1196
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The section <literal>/general/signature_handling</literal> can be used to "
"specify a different behavior."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1200
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;general&gt;\n"
"  &lt;signature-handling&gt;\n"
"    &lt;accept_unknown_gpg_key config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/"
"accept_unknown_gpg_key&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/signature-handling&gt;\n"
"&lt;/general&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1208
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reporting"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <literal>report</literal> resource manages three types of pop-ups that "
"may appear during installation:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1217
#, no-c-format
msgid "message pop-ups (usually non-critical, informative messages),"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1222
#, no-c-format
msgid "warning pop-ups (if something might go wrong),"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1227
#, no-c-format
msgid "error pop-ups (in case an error occurs)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1234
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reporting Behavior"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1235
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;report&gt;\n"
"  &lt;errors&gt;\n"
"    &lt;show config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/show&gt;\n"
"    &lt;timeout config:type=\"integer\"&gt;0&lt;/timeout&gt;\n"
"    &lt;log config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/log&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/errors&gt;\n"
"  &lt;warnings&gt;\n"
"    &lt;show config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/show&gt;\n"
"    &lt;timeout config:type=\"integer\"&gt;10&lt;/timeout&gt;\n"
"    &lt;log config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/log&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/warnings&gt;\n"
"  &lt;messages&gt;\n"
"    &lt;show config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/show&gt;\n"
"    &lt;timeout config:type=\"integer\"&gt;10&lt;/timeout&gt;\n"
"    &lt;log config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/log&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/messages&gt;\n"
"  &lt;yesno_messages&gt;\n"
"    &lt;show config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/show&gt;\n"
"    &lt;timeout config:type=\"integer\"&gt;10&lt;/timeout&gt;\n"
"    &lt;log config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/log&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/yesno_messages&gt;\n"
"&lt;/report&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1259
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Depending on your experience, you can skip, log and show (with timeout) "
"those messages. It is recommended to show all <literal>messages</literal> "
"with timeout. Warnings can be skipped in some places but should not be "
"ignored."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1266
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The default setting in auto-installation mode is to show errors without "
"timeout and to show all warnings/messages with a timeout of 10 seconds."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1273
#, no-c-format
msgid "Critical System Messages"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1274
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that not all messages during installation are controlled by the "
"<literal>report</literal> resource. Some critical messages concerning "
"package installation and partitioning will show up ignoring your settings in "
"the <literal>report</literal> section. Usually those messages will need to "
"be answered with <guimenu>Yes</guimenu> or <guimenu>No</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1285
#, no-c-format
msgid "System Registration and Extension Selection"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1287
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Registering the system with the can be configured within the "
"<literal>suse_register</literal> resource. The following example registers "
"the system with the &scc;. In case your organization provides its own "
"registration server, you need to specify the required data with the "
"<literal>reg_server*</literal> properties. Refer to the table below for "
"details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1296
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;suse_register&gt;\n"
"  &lt;do_registration config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/"
"do_registration&gt;\n"
"  &lt;email&gt;&exampleuser_plain;@&exampledomain;&lt;/email&gt;\n"
"  &lt;reg_code&gt;<replaceable>MY_SECRET_REGCODE</replaceable>&lt;/"
"reg_code&gt;\n"
"  &lt;install_updates config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/"
"install_updates&gt;\n"
"  &lt;slp_discovery config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;false&lt;/slp_discovery&gt;\n"
"&lt;/suse_register&gt;\n"
" "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1305
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As an alternative to the fully automated registration, &ay; can also be "
"configured to start the &yast; registration module during the installation. "
"This offers the possibility to enter the registration data manually. The "
"following XML code is required:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1312
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;general&gt;\n"
" &lt;semi-automatic config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"   &lt;semi-automatic_entry&gt;scc&lt;/semi-automatic_entry&gt;\n"
" &lt;/semi-automatic&gt;\n"
"&lt;/general&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1319
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using the Installation Network Settings"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1320
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case you need to use the same network settings that were used for the "
"installation, &ay; needs to run the network setup in stage 1 right before "
"the registration is started:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1325
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;networking&gt;\n"
"  &lt;setup_before_proposal config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/"
"setup_before_proposal&gt;\n"
"&lt;/networking&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1354
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>do_registration</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1362
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;do_registration config:type=\"boolean\"\n"
"&gt;true&lt;/do_registration&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1366
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specify whether the system should be registered or not. If set to "
"<literal>false</literal> all other options are ignored and the system is not "
"registered."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1375
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>e-mail</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1380
#, no-c-format
msgid "E-mail address"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1383
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;email&gt;&exampleuser_plain;@&exampledomain;&lt;/email&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1386
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optional. The e-mail address matching the registration code."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1393
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>reg_code</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1401
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;reg_code&gt;<replaceable>SECRET_REGCODE</replaceable>&lt;/reg_code&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1404
#, no-c-format
msgid "Required. Registration code."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1411
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>install_updates</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1419
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;install_updates config:type=\"boolean\"\n"
"&gt;true&lt;/install_updates&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1423
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optional. Determines if updates from the Updates channels should be "
"installed. The default value is to not install them ( <literal>false</"
"literal> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1431
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>slp_discovery</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1439
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;slp_discovery config:type=\"boolean\"\n"
"&gt;true&lt;/slp_discovery&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1443
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optional. Search for a registration server via SLP. The default value is "
"<literal>false</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1447
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Expects to find a single server. If more than one server is found, the "
"installation will fail. In case there is more than one registration server "
"available, you need to specify one with <literal>reg_server</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1453
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If neither <literal>slp_discovery</literal> nor <literal>reg_server</"
"literal> are set, the system is registered with the &scc;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1458
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This setting also affects the self-update feature: If it is disabled, no SLP "
"search will be performed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1466
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>reg_server</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1474
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;reg_server&gt;\n"
"  https://smt.&exampledomain;\n"
"&lt;/reg_server&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1479
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optional. &rmt; server URL. If neither <literal>slp_discovery</literal> nor "
"<literal>reg_server</literal> are set, the system is registered with the "
"&scc;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1484
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &rmt; server is queried for a URL of the self-update repository. So if "
"<literal>self_update_url</literal> is not set, the &rmt; server influences "
"where the self-updates are downloaded from. Check out the &deploy; to find "
"further information about this feature."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1494
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>reg_server_cert_fingerprint_type</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1499
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>SHA1</literal> or <literal>SHA256</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1502
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;reg_server_cert_fingerprint_type&gt;\n"
"  SHA1\n"
"&lt;/reg_server_cert_fingerprint_type&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1507
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optional. Requires a checksum value provided with "
"<literal>reg_server_cert_fingerprint</literal> . Using the fingerprint is "
"recommended, since it ensures the SSL certificate is verified. The matching "
"certificate will be automatically imported when the SSL communication fails "
"because of a verification error."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1518
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>reg_server_cert_fingerprint</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1523
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Server Certificate Fingerprint value in hexadecimal notion (case-"
"insensitive)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1526
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;reg_server_cert_fingerprint&gt;\n"
"  <replaceable>01:AB...:EF</replaceable>\n"
"&lt;/reg_server_cert_fingerprint&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1531
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optional. Requires a fingerprint type value provided with "
"<literal>reg_server_cert_fingerprint_type</literal> . Using the fingerprint "
"is recommended, since it ensures the SSL certificate is verified. The "
"matching certificate will be automatically imported when the SSL "
"communication fails because of a verification error."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1542
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>reg_server_cert</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1547
#, no-c-format
msgid "URL"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1550
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;reg_server_cert&gt;\n"
"  http://smt.&exampledomain;/smt.crt\n"
"&lt;/reg_server_cert&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1555
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optional. URL of the SSL certificate on the server. Using this option is not "
"recommended, since the certificate that is downloaded is not verified. Use "
"<literal>reg_server_cert_fingerprint</literal> instead."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1564
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>addons</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1569
#, no-c-format
msgid "Add-ons list"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1574
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specify an extension from the registration server that should be added to "
"the installation repositories. See <xref linkend=\"CreateProfile.Register."
"Extension\"/> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1586
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating Own Server Certificate Fingerprint"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1587
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In order to generate a new Server Certificate Fingerprint for the entry "
"<literal>reg_server_cert_fingerprint</literal> you can use the following "
"command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1592
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"echo | openssl s_client -showcerts -connect scc.suse.com:443 2&gt; /dev/null "
"|\n"
"openssl x509 -noout -fingerprint -sha256\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1596
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Replace <literal>scc.suse.com</literal> with your server, optionally use "
"<literal>-sha1</literal> instead of <literal>-sha256</literal> (but the "
"SHA256 default is better)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1601
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>NOTE: </emphasis> This can be used in a trusted network only! In a "
"non-trusted network, for example the Internet, you should get the "
"fingerprint directly from the server by other means. Fingerprints can be "
"fetched via SSH, a saved server configuration and other sources. "
"Alternatively, you can verify that the downloaded certificate is exactly the "
"same as on the server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1612
#, no-c-format
msgid "Extensions"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1613
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &scc; provides several extensions, such as <literal>sle-module-"
"development-tools</literal> (Development Tools Module) that can be included "
"as additional sources during the installation. Adding extensions can be done "
"via the <literal>addons</literal> property within the "
"<literal>suse_register</literal> block. <!-- Below is a list of all "
"extensions available for &productname; on x86_64: -->"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1624
#, no-c-format
msgid "Availability of Extensions"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1625
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The availability of extensions is product and architecture dependent, not "
"all extensions are available on all architectures. <!-- All listed "
"extensions are available for &sls; on the x86_64 architecture. -->"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1631
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some extensions, such as <literal>sle-ha</literal> , require a registration "
"code. Depending on your subscription, either use a dedicated registration "
"code for the extension, or restate the code for the base product."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1639
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With <command>SUSEConnect --list-extensions</command> you can list all "
"available extensions in a registered system. The result contains lines like:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1643
#, no-c-format
msgid "Install with: SUSEConnect -p sle-module-development-tools/15/x86_64"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1644
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <option>-p</option> argument displays the <replaceable>NAME/VERSION/"
"ARCH</replaceable> values that can be used in the AutoYaST profile as "
"follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1649
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<![CDATA[<addons config:type=\"list\">\n"
" <addon>\n"
"  <!-- Development Tools Module -->\n"
"  <name>sle-module-development-tools</name>\n"
"  <version>15</version>\n"
"  <arch>x86_64</arch>\n"
" </addon>\n"
"</addons>]]>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1659
#, no-c-format
msgid "Extension Dependencies"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1660
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since &slsa; 15, &ay; automatically reorders the extensions according to "
"their dependencies during registration. This means the order of the "
"extensions in the &ay; profile is not important."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1665
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Also &ay; automatically registers the dependent extensions even though they "
"are missing in the profile. This means you are not required to fill the "
"extensions list completely."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1670
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"However, if the dependent extension requires a registration key, this must "
"be specified in the profile, including the registration key. Otherwise the "
"registration would fail."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1677
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For background information and add-on listings for &slsa; see <link xlink:"
"href=\"https://github.com/yast/yast-registration/wiki/Available-SCC-"
"Extensions-for-Use-in-Autoyast\"/> . The listings will get updated from time "
"to time."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1686
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Boot Loader"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1688
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This documentation is for <command>yast2-bootloader</command> and applies to "
"&grub;. For older product versions shipping with legacy GRUB, refer to the "
"documentation that comes with your distribution in <filename>/usr/share/doc/"
"packages/autoyast2/</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1695
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The general structure of the &ay; boot loader part looks like the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1700
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;bootloader&gt;\n"
"  &lt;loader_type&gt;\n"
"    &lt;!-- boot loader type (grub2 or grub2-efi) --&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/loader_type&gt;\n"
"  &lt;global&gt;\n"
"    &lt;!--\n"
"      entries defining the installation settings for &grub; and\n"
"      the generic boot code\n"
"    --&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/global&gt;\n"
"  &lt;device_map config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"    &lt;!-- entries defining the order of devices --&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/device_map&gt;\n"
" &lt;/bootloader&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1716
#, no-c-format
msgid "Loader Type"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1717
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This defines which boot loader (UEFI or BIOS/legacy) to use. Not all "
"architectures support both legacy and EFI variants of the boot loader. The "
"safest ( <literal>default</literal> ) option is to leave the decision up to "
"the installer."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1723
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;loader_type&gt;<replaceable>LOADER_TYPE</replaceable>&lt;/loader_type&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1724
#, no-c-format
msgid "Possible values for <replaceable>LOADER_TYPE</replaceable> are:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1729
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>default</literal> : The installer chooses the correct boot loader. "
"This is the default when no option is defined."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1735
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>grub2</literal> : Use the legacy BIOS boot loader."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1740
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>grub2-efi</literal> : Use the EFI boot loader."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1745
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>none</literal> : The boot process is not managed and configured by "
"the installer."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1754
#, no-c-format
msgid "Globals"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1755
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is an important if optional part. Define here where to install &grub; "
"and how the boot process will work. Again, <command>yast2-bootloader</"
"command> proposes a configuration if you do not define one. Usually the &ay; "
"control file includes only this part and all other parts are added "
"automatically during installation by <command>yast2-bootloader</command> . "
"Unless you have some special requirements, do not specify the boot loader "
"configuration in the XML file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1765
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;global&gt;\n"
"  &lt;activate config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/activate&gt;\n"
"  &lt;timeout config:type=\"integer\"&gt;10&lt;/timeout&gt;\n"
"  &lt;suse_btrfs config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/suse_btrfs&gt;\n"
"  &lt;terminal&gt;gfxterm&lt;/terminal&gt;\n"
"  &lt;gfxmode&gt;1280x1024x24&lt;/gfxmode&gt;\n"
"&lt;/global&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1791
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>activate</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1796
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set the boot flag on the boot partition. The boot partition can be "
"<filename>/</filename> if there is no separate /boot partition. If the boot "
"partition is on a logical partition, the boot flag is set to the extended "
"partition."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1802
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;activate config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/activate&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1807
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>append</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1812
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Kernel parameters added at the end of boot entries for normal and recovery "
"mode."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1821
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>boot_boot</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1826
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Write &grub; to a separate /boot partition. If no separate /boot partition "
"exists, &grub; will be written to <filename>/</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1831
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;boot_boot&gt;false&lt;/boot_boot&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1836
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>boot_custom</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1841
#, no-c-format
msgid "Write &grub; to a custom device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1844
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;boot_custom&gt;/dev/sda3&lt;/boot_custom&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1849
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>boot_extended</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1854
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Write &grub; to the extended partition (important if you want to use a "
"generic boot code and the <filename>/boot</filename> partition is logical). "
"NOTE: if the boot partition is logical, you should use <literal>boot_mbr</"
"literal> (write &grub; to MBR) rather than <literal>generic_mbr</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1861
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;boot_extended&gt;false&lt;/boot_extended&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1866
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>boot_mbr</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1871
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Write &grub; to MBR of the first disk in the order (device.map includes "
"order of disks)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1875
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;boot_mbr&gt;false&lt;/boot_mbr&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1880
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>boot_root</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1885
#, no-c-format
msgid "Write &grub; to <filename>/</filename> partition."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1888
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;boot_root&gt;false&lt;/boot_root&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1893
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>generic_mbr</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1898
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Write generic boot code to MBR, will be ignored if boot_mbr is set to "
"<literal>true</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1902
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;generic_mbr config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;false&lt;/generic_mbr&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1907
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>gfxmode</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1912
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Graphical resolution of the &grub; screen (requires &lt;terminal&gt; to be "
"set to <literal>gfxterm</literal> . Valid entries are <literal>auto</"
"literal> , <literal><replaceable>HORIZONTAL</"
"replaceable>x<replaceable>VERTICAL</replaceable></literal> , or "
