msgid "<literal>auditd/flush</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9064
#, no-c-format
msgid "Describes how to write the data to disk."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9069
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If set to <literal>INCREMENTAL</literal> the Frequency parameter tells how "
"many records to write before issuing an explicit flush to disk. "
"<literal>NONE</literal> means: no special effort is made to flush data, "
"<literal>DATA</literal> : keep data portion synchronized, <literal>SYNC</"
"literal> : keep data and metadata fully synchronized."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9080
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>auditd/freq</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9085
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This parameter tells how many records to write before issuing an explicit "
"flush to disk."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9090
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The parameter <literal>flush</literal> needs to be set to "
"<literal>INCREMENTAL</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9097
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>auditd/log_file</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9102
#, no-c-format
msgid "The full path name to the log file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9113
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>auditd/log_fomat</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9123
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set <literal>RAW</literal> to log all data (store in a format exactly as the "
"kernel sends it) or <literal>NOLOG</literal> to discard all audit "
"information instead of writing it to disk (does not affect data sent to the "
"dispatcher)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9132
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>auditd/max_log_file</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9137
#, no-c-format
msgid "How much information needs to be logged."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9142
#, no-c-format
msgid "Unit: Megabytes"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9149
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>auditd/num_logs</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9154
#, no-c-format
msgid "Number of log files."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9159
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>max_log_file_action</literal> needs to be set to <literal>ROTATE</"
"literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9166
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>auditd/max_log_file_action</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9171
#, no-c-format
msgid "What happens if the log capacity has been reached."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9176
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the action is set to <literal>ROTATE</literal> the Number of Log Files "
"specifies the number of files to keep. Set to <literal>SYSLOG</literal> , "
"the audit daemon will write a warning to the system log. With "
"<literal>SUSPEND</literal> the daemon stops writing records to disk. "
"<literal>IGNORE</literal> means do nothing, <literal>KEEP_LOGS</literal> is "
"similar to <literal>ROTATE</literal> , but log files are not overwritten."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9189
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>auditd/name_format</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9194
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Computer Name Format describes how to write the computer name to the log "
"file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9199
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If <literal>USER</literal> is set, the User Defined Name is used. "
"<literal>NONE</literal> means no computer name is inserted. "
"<literal>HOSTNAME</literal> uses the name returned by the 'gethostname' "
"syscall. <literal>FQD</literal> uses the fully qualified domain name."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9209
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>rules</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9214
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rules for auditctl"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9219
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can edit the rules manually, which we only recommend for advanced users. "
"For more information about all options, see <command>man auditctl</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9233
#, no-c-format
msgid "Users and Groups"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9235
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"AutoYaST supports defining local users, groups, special login settings and "
"even default options for new users. Those settings are defined in the "
"following sections:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9242
#, no-c-format
msgid "users"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9244
#, no-c-format
msgid "List of users"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9250
#, no-c-format
msgid "user_defaults"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9252
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default options for new users"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9258
#, no-c-format
msgid "groups"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9260
#, no-c-format
msgid "List of groups"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9266
#, no-c-format
msgid "login_settings"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9268
#, no-c-format
msgid "Special login settings like password-less login or autologin"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9276
#, no-c-format
msgid "Users and groups set up during the first stage"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9277
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Users and groups are set up during the first stage, so you can set up a "
"usable system without running the second stage."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9284
#, no-c-format
msgid "Users"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9286
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A list of users can be defined in the <literal>&lt;users&gt;</literal> "
"section. To be able to log in, make sure that either the &rootuser; users "
"are set up or rootpassword is specified as a linuxrc option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9293
#, no-c-format
msgid "Minimal User Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9294
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;users config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;user&gt;\n"
"    &lt;username&gt;root&lt;/username&gt;\n"
"    &lt;user_password&gt;password&lt;/user_password&gt;\n"
"    &lt;encrypted config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;false&lt;/encrypted&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/user&gt;\n"
"    &lt;user&gt;\n"
"    &lt;username&gt;&exampleuser_plain;&lt;/username&gt;\n"
"    &lt;user_password&gt;password&lt;/user_password&gt;\n"
"    &lt;encrypted config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;false&lt;/encrypted&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/user&gt;\n"
"&lt;/users&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:9308
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following example shows a more complex scenario. System wide default "
"settings from <filename>/etc/default/useradd</filename> , such as the shell "
"or the parent directory for the home directory, are applied."
